<paragraph blockId="11.[809,1426,1487,1693]" pageId="11">
<emphasis box="[809,899,1487,1508]" italics="true" pageId="11">Adults:</emphasis>
Body slender. Head mostly concealed by pronotum, rostrate. Rostrum short to moderately long, often very stout. Pronotum widest at base, with rectangular to slightly projected posterior angles, variable in shape. Elytra without sexual dimorphism, moderately dilated posteriorly in both sexes, with four indistinct costae in each elytron (
<figureCitation box="[1219,1409,1671,1693]" captionStart="Figure 7" captionStartId="12.[163,242,1805,1827]" captionTargetBox="[227,1379,198,1757]" captionTargetId="figure-25@12.[224,1382,195,1765]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="Figure 7. General appearance. A, Lipernes sp. 3, male. B, Lipernes sp. 1, male. C, Lipernes sp. 1, female. D, Lipernes sp. 2, male. E, ditto, female. F, Lipernes sp. 4, male. G, Lipernes sp. 5, male. H, Lipernes sp. 6, male. I, Lipernes sp. 7, male. J, Lipernes sp. 8, male. K, Lipernes sp. 9, male. L, Lipernes sp. 13, male. M, Lipernes sp. 14, male. N, Lipernes sp. 14, male. O," figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5299927" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5299927/files/figure.png" pageId="11">Fig. 7A–O, R–U</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
